{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Use Australian English|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox Australian rules football season | competition = VFA Premiership season | year = 1917 VFA | image = | imagesize = | caption = | teams = | premiers = ''Premiership not contested'' | count = | minor premiers = | mpcount = <!-- Counted only since 1903, when finals were first introduced --> | pre-season name = | pre-season cup = | pscount = | matches = | attendance = | highattend = | leading goal medal = | brownlow medal = | prevseason = [[1916 VFA season|1916]] | nextseason = [[1918 VFA season|1918]] }}
The '''1917 [[Victorian Football Association]] season''' was not played owing to [[World War I]], which was at its peak at the time.
==Abandonment of the season== To support the war effort in [[World War I]], the Association had curtailed its [[1915 VFA season|1915 season]] by five weeks,<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Argus|publication-place=Melbourne, VIC|title=Association season curtailed|date=15 July 1915|page=8}}</ref> and then cancelled its [[1916 VFA season|1916 season]] entirely.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Argus|date=26 February 1916|publication-place=Melbourne, VIC|page=18|title=Football and war}}</ref> With the war still ongoing, the Association voted on 5 February 1917 to cancel the 1917 season as well.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Argus|date=6 February 1917|publication-place=Melbourne, VIC|page=8|title=Sport and war}}</ref> 1917 was the last Association season cancelled during World War I, with a premiership season held in [[1918 VFA season|1918]] with a reduced number of clubs.
