The '''Jersey Shore Music Festival''' is an annual free-admission music event within the Jersey Shore Festival. The first Jersey Shore Music Festival took place on May 17 and 18, 2013 in [[Seaside Heights]], [[New Jersey]]. The first annual event featured more than 40 bands in variety of musical genres including [[rock music|rock]], [[singer-songwriter]], [[alternative rock|alternative]], [[pop rock]], and others. Performances took place outdoors near other Jersey Shore Festival events,<ref>{{cite web|last=Jordan|first=Chris|title=A Freewheelin Festival|url=http://www.app.com/article/20130516/NJENT/305160073/A-freewheelin-festival|publisher=APP.com}}</ref> as well as inside bars on the Seaside Heights boardwalk.<ref>{{cite web|title=Your Guide to the Jersey Shore Festival|url=http://speakimge.com/your-guide-to-jersey-shore-festival-simges-showcase-local-performances-not-to-miss-more-to-see-at-seaside/|author=Chris Rotolo|year=2013|publisher=Speak Into My Good Eye}}</ref>
The first annual Jersey Shore Music Festival was one of Seaside Heights' first major events<ref>{{cite web|last=Pfeiffer|first=John|title=Jersey Shore's First Major Event of Post-Sandy Summer Season|url=http://sparkle-trash.blogspot.com/2013/05/jersey-shores-first-major-event-of-post.html?q=jersey+shore+festival|publisher=Sparkle Trash}}</ref> since October 2012 storm [[Hurricane Sandy]], which had previously caused damage to more than half of the town's homes and businesses.<ref>{{cite web|last=Davis|first=Tom|title=Hurricane Sandy Damaged 60 Percent of Seaside Heights Homes|url=http://tomsriver.patch.com/groups/politics-and-elections/p/hurricane-sandy-damaged-60-percent-of-seaside-heights-homes|publisher=Toms River Patch}}</ref> The festival's other events included the Jersey Shore Car Show, [[Freestyle Motocross]], [[Bicycle motocross|BMX]], and [[Skateboarding|Skateboard]] stunt shows, a vendor village, and [[paintball]] target practice.
The 2nd Annual Jersey Shore Music Festival will be held on May 16 and 17, 2014 as part of the Jersey Shore Festival.{{citation needed|date=July 2013}}
